transcription.text:
Speaker 1: How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm still trying to get a refund.

Speaker 1: Yeah, well, did you send the product back?

Speaker 2: When was it sent back to us?

Speaker 1: No, I never sent it back.

Speaker 2: I've left messages.

Speaker 1: I've tried to talk to somebody.

Speaker 2: We're trying to get it returned.

Speaker 1: I don't know where to send it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so the return address is in the back of the bottle.

Speaker 1: All you do is include a note with a first and last name,

Speaker 2: and you just send it to that address.

Speaker 1: Okay. How do we know we get refunded?

Speaker 2: Well, you'll see it on your statements.

Speaker 1: It'll be sent out to you, but first, you need to send it back.

Speaker 2: Oh, I get that.

Speaker 1: I understand you don't get a refund until it's sent back,

Speaker 2: but there needs to be some ...

Speaker 1: There is no confirmation or nothing we can send you.

Speaker 2: You'll just see it in your billing statements.

Speaker 1: That's usually how every other refund works

Speaker 2: with any other customer we have.

Speaker 1: Okay. We'll send one back today. Thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem. Have a good one.
